Grandview Triangle.label: Grandview Triangle
Grandview Triangle.description: The 3-Trails Crossing Memorial Highway is the official name for a highway interchange in south Kansas City, Missouri that was once considered one of Missouri's most congested locations. Wikipedia

El Toro Y.label: El Toro Y
El Toro Y.description: The El Toro "Y" is a freeway interchange in southern Orange County, California where the Santa Ana Freeway, Interstate 5, and the San Diego Freeway, the I-405 merge. Wikipedia

Newark Airport Interchange.label: Newark Airport Interchange
Newark Airport Interchange.description: The Newark Airport Interchange is a massive interchange of Interstate 78, U.S. Route 1-9, U.S. Route 22, New Jersey Route 21, and Interstate 95 at the northern edge of Newark Liberty International Airport in Newark, New Jersey. Wikipedia

Central Motorway Junction.label: Central Motorway Junction
Central Motorway Junction.description: The Central Motorway Junction or CMJ, is the intersection of New Zealand State Highways 1 and 16, just south of the central business district of Auckland. Wikipedia

Braintree Split.label: Braintree Split
Braintree Split.description: The Braintree Split is the intersection of Interstate 93/U.S. Route 1 and Massachusetts Route 3 located along the city line separating Braintree and Quincy, Massachusetts. Wikipedia

Anna Flyover.label: Anna Flyover
Anna Flyover.description: Anna Flyover, also known as Gemini Flyover, is a dual-armed flyover in the central business district of Chennai, India. Wikipedia

Cemetery Junction, Reading.label: Cemetery Junction, Reading
Cemetery Junction, Reading.description: Cemetery Junction is a road junction in East Reading, bordering on Newtown, in the town of Reading in the English county of Berkshire. Wikipedia

South Bay Interchange.label: South Bay Interchange
South Bay Interchange.description: The South Bay Interchange is a massive interchange in the South Bay region of Boston, Massachusetts, in the US. Wikipedia

Zoo Interchange.label: Zoo Interchange
Zoo Interchange.description: The Zoo Interchange is a freeway Interchange on the west side of Milwaukee, Wisconsin. It was built in 1963, as one of the first Interstate Highway projects in Wisconsin. It forms the junction of I-94, I-894, and US 45. Wikipedia

East Los Angeles Interchange.label: East Los Angeles Interchange
East Los Angeles Interchange.description: The East Los Angeles Interchange complex is the busiest freeway interchange in the world, with its southern portion handling over 550,000 vehicles per day. Wikipedia

Anna J. Cooper Circle.label: Anna J. Cooper Circle
Anna J. Cooper Circle.description: Anna J. Cooper Circle is a traffic circle and park at the intersection of 3rd and T Streets, Northwest, in the historic LeDroit Park neighborhood of Washington, D.C. Wikipedia
Anna J. Cooper Circle.type: Street in Washington, D.C., United States of America

Bank junction.label: Bank junction
Bank junction.description: Bank junction is a major road junction in the City of London, the historic and financial centre of London, at which nine streets converge on an area where traffic is controlled by traffic lights and give-way lines. Wikipedia

Kanfanar interchange.label: Kanfanar interchange
Kanfanar interchange.description: The Kanfanar interchange is a cloverleaf interchange west of Kanfanar, Croatia. The interchange represents the western terminus of the A8 motorway and it connects the A8 route to the A9 motorway ... Wikipedia

Penns Neck Circle.label: Penns Neck Circle
Penns Neck Circle.description: Penns Neck Circle is a traffic circle in West Windsor Township, New Jersey. It is located at the junction of US 1 and Washington Road. It is a major intersection, as Washington Road is one of three connections between US 1 and Princeton, New Jersey. Wikipedia

Tetteh Quarshie Interchange.label: Tetteh Quarshie Interchange
Tetteh Quarshie Interchange.description: The Tetteh Quarshie Interchange is a cloverleaf interchange carrying a six-lane motorway that links the Liberation Road from 37 military hospital to the Pantang junction through Madina in Accra, Ghana. Wikipedia

Makupa Circus.label: Makupa Circus
Makupa Circus.description:
The Makupa Circus is a primary road junction in Mombasa, Kenya. The roundabout is situated in the Makupa district of the island.
The roundabout serves the majority of migrating traffic in Mombasa. Wikipedia

College Park Interchange.label: Interstate 495
College Park Interchange.description: Interstate 495 is a 64-mile Interstate Highway that surrounds Washington, D.C., the capital of the United States of America, and the city's inner suburbs in adjacent Maryland and Virginia. Wikipedia

Bruckner Interchange.label: Bruckner Interchange
Bruckner Interchange.description: The Bruckner Interchange is a complex interchange in the New York City borough of the Bronx in the United States. The junction connects four highways the Bruckner, Cross Bronx, and Hutchinson River expressways, and the Hutchinson River Parkway. Wikipedia
Bruckner Interchange.type: Highway in New York City, New York

Downtown freeway loop.label: Downtown freeway loop
Downtown freeway loop.description: The downtown loop, also nicknamed the "Alphabet Loop", is a complex layout of highways in downtown Kansas City, Missouri involving 23 exits, four Interstate Highways, four U.S. Highways and numerous city streets. Wikipedia

Kellogg Interchange.label: Kellogg Interchange
Kellogg Interchange.description: The Kellogg Interchange complex is a freeway interchange in Southern California. The interchange is located at the boundary between the cities of San Dimas and Pomona about 25 miles east of downtown Los Angeles. It is named for the nearby W. K. Wikipedia

MacArthur Maze.label: MacArthur Maze
MacArthur Maze.description: The MacArthur Maze is a large freeway interchange located near the eastern end of the San Francisco–Oakland Bay Bridge in Oakland, California. Wikipedia

Four Mile Circle.label: Four Mile Circle
Four Mile Circle.description: Four Mile Circle is a traffic circle in the U.S. state of New Jersey. It is located at the junction of Route 70, Route 72, Buddtown Road, and New Lisbon Road. Wikipedia

Sam Yan.label: Sam Yan
Sam Yan.description: Sam Yan is the name of an intersection and its nearby neighbourhood in Bangkok, Thailand. It connects Rama IV Road with Phaya Thai Road to the north and Si Phraya Road to the south, and is located within ... Wikipedia

Orange Crush interchange.label: Orange Crush interchange
Orange Crush interchange.description: The Orange Crush Interchange is a freeway interchange in the city of Orange, California, near the confluence of the cities of Orange, Santa Ana, Anaheim, and Garden Grove. Wikipedia

Los Alamitos Circle.label: Traffic Circle
Los Alamitos Circle.description: The Los Alamitos Traffic Circle, informally known as the Long Beach Traffic Circle, is a roundabout at the intersection of Lakewood Boulevard, Pacific Coast Highway and Los Coyotes Diagonal in Long Beach, California. Wikipedia

SuperRedTan Interchange.label: SuperRedTan Interchange
SuperRedTan Interchange.description: The SuperRedTan Interchange is a symmetrical four-level freeway interchange in eastern Mesa, Arizona. Completed in 2007, the interchange provides access between U.S. Route 60 and Loop 202. Wikipedia

Chevy Chase Circle.label: Chevy Chase Circle
Chevy Chase Circle.description: Chevy Chase Circle is a traffic circle straddling the border of Chevy Chase, Washington, D.C. and Chevy Chase, Maryland. Wikipedia

Chennai Airport Flyover.label: Chennai Airport Flyover
Chennai Airport Flyover.description: Chennai Airport Flyover is a 1.6 km long flyover in front of the Chennai International Airport in Chennai city. Wikipedia

Orehovica interchange.label: Orehovica interchange
Orehovica interchange.description: The Orehovica interchange is a trumpet interchange in Rijeka, Croatia. The interchange represents the southern terminus of the A6 motorway and it connects the A6 route to the A7 motorway between Škurinje ... Wikipedia

Ngauranga Interchange.label: Ngauranga Interchange
Ngauranga Interchange.description: The Ngauranga Interchange is a major interchange in the suburb of Ngauranga, in Wellington City, New Zealand. Wikipedia

Turcot Interchange.label: Turcot Interchange
Turcot Interchange.description: The Turcot Interchange is a three-level stack freeway interchange within the city of Montreal, Quebec, Canada. Located southwest of downtown, the interchange links highways 15, 20, and 720, and provides access to the Champlain Bridge. Wikipedia

Madhya Kailash Junction.label: Madhya Kailash Junction
Madhya Kailash Junction.description: The Madhya Kailash Junction is an important junction in the southern part of the city of Chennai. It is located at the beginning of the Rajiv Gandhi Salai which intersects the Sardar Patel Road in the form of "T". Wikipedia

Spaghetti Bowl (Las Vegas).label: Spaghetti Bowl
Spaghetti Bowl (Las Vegas).description: The Spaghetti Bowl is the colloquial name for a freeway interchange near downtown Las Vegas, Nevada. It is the intersection of Interstate 15, U.S. Route 95 and Interstate 515, as well as Martin Luther King Blvd. Wikipedia

Circle Interchange.label: Circle Interchange
Circle Interchange.description: The Circle Interchange is an expressway interchange near downtown Chicago, Illinois. It is the junction between the Dan Ryan, Kennedy and Eisenhower Expressways, and Congress Parkway. Wikipedia

Pinehurst Circle.label: Pinehurst Circle
Pinehurst Circle.description: Pinehurst Circle is at the intersection of Western and Utah Avenues and 33rd and Worthington Streets in Northwest Washington, D.C. Wikipedia
Pinehurst Circle.type: Avenue in Washington, D.C., United States of America

Judge Harry Pregerson Interchange.label: Judge Harry Pregerson Interchange
Judge Harry Pregerson Interchange.description: The Judge Harry Pregerson Interchange is a stack interchange near the Athens and Watts communities of Los Angeles, California. Wikipedia

Magic Roundabout (Swindon).label: Magic Roundabout
Magic Roundabout (Swindon).description: The Magic Roundabout in Swindon, England was constructed in 1972 and consists of five mini-roundabouts arranged around a sixth central, anti-clockwise roundabout. It is located near the County Ground, home of Swindon Town F.C. Wikipedia

Kathipara Junction.label: Kathipara Junction
Kathipara Junction.description: Kathipara Junction is an important road junction in Chennai, India. It is located at Alandur, south of Guindy, at the intersection of the Grand Southern Trunk Road, Inner Ring Road, Anna Salai and the Mount-Poonamallee Road. Wikipedia

Mousetrap (Denver).label: Mousetrap
Mousetrap (Denver).description: The Mousetrap is an informal name for the interchange of Interstate 25 and Interstate 70 in the northern part of Denver, Colorado, USA. Wikipedia

Interstate 95 Interchange Project.label: Pennsylvania Turnpike/Interstate 95 Interchange Project
Interstate 95 Interchange Project.description: The Pennsylvania Turnpike/Interstate 95 Interchange Project is a project in the United States to build an interchange where Interstate 95 crosses the Pennsylvania Turnpike in Bristol Township, Pennsylvania. Wikipedia
Interstate 95 Interchange Project.type: Turnpike in United States of America

High Five Interchange.label: High Five Interchange
High Five Interchange.description: The High Five Interchange is the first five-level stack interchange built in Dallas, Texas. Located at the junction of the Lyndon B. Johnson Freeway and the Central Expressway, it replaces an antiquated ... Wikipedia

Kennedy Interchange.label: Kennedy Interchange
Kennedy Interchange.description: The Kennedy Interchange, unofficially, though universally, referred to as Spaghetti Junction, is the intersection of Interstates 64, 65 and 71 at the northeastern edge of downtown Louisville, Kentucky, USA. Wikipedia

Red Cow interchange.label: Red Cow interchange
Red Cow interchange.description: The Red Cow interchange is a major road junction in west Dublin, Ireland on the M50, meeting the N7 Naas Road at a free-flow grade separated junction which incorporates a light railway line. Wikipedia

Barney Circle.label: Barney Circle
Barney Circle.description: Barney Circle is a small neighborhood located on the western bank of the Anacostia River in southeast Washington, D.C. The "circle" refers to the traffic circle that intersects Pennsylvania Avenue SE as it crosses the Anacostia. Wikipedia

Four Level Interchange.label: Four Level Interchange
Four Level Interchange.description: The Four Level Interchange was the first stack interchange in the world. Completed in 1949 and fully opened in 1953 at the northern edge of Downtown Los Angeles, California, USA, it connects U.S. Route 101 to State Route 110. Wikipedia

Alemany Maze.label: Alemany Maze
Alemany Maze.description: Alemany Maze is the name given to the interchange between the James Lick Freeway and the John F. Foran Freeway in the city of San Francisco. An alternative name for this highway feature is the Alemany Interchange. Wikipedia

Golden Glades Interchange.label: Golden Glades Interchange
Golden Glades Interchange.description: The Golden Glades Interchange, located in Miami Gardens and North Miami Beach, Florida, United States, is the confluence of five major roads serving eastern and southern Florida. Wikipedia

Marquette Interchange.label: Marquette Interchange
Marquette Interchange.description: The Marquette Interchange is a major freeway interchange in downtown Milwaukee, Wisconsin, located near Marquette University where Interstate 43, Interstate 94, Interstate 794, and U.S. Highway 41 meet. Wikipedia

Rainbow Interchange.label: Rainbow Interchange
Rainbow Interchange.description: The Rainbow Interchange is one of two named interchanges in southeastern Florida. It is a four-level stack interchange near Fort Lauderdale-Hollywood International Airport in Fort Lauderdale, Florida. Wikipedia

Midtown Interchange.label: Midtown Interchange
Midtown Interchange.description: The Midtown Interchange, located in the Civic Center and Overtown neighborhoods of Miami, Florida, USA, is the convergence of three major motorways I-95, I-395, and the Dolphin Expressway. Wikipedia
